    <item>
      <title>Vitamin D and Zinc are crucial for the immune system (viral infection, etc.)</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/posts/vitamin-d-and-zinc-are-crucial-for-the-immune-system-viral-infection-etc/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 08 Mar 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/posts/vitamin-d-and-zinc-are-crucial-for-the-immune-system-viral-infection-etc/</guid>
      <description>&lt;nav id=&#34;TableOfContents&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;ul&gt;&#xA;    &lt;li&gt;&#xA;      &lt;ul&gt;&#xA;        &lt;li&gt;&#xA;          &lt;ul&gt;&#xA;            &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#immunomodulatory-effects-of-vitamin-d-and-zinc-on-viral-infection&#34;&gt;Immunomodulatory Effects of Vitamin D and Zinc on Viral Infection&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;          &lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;        &lt;/li&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/li&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;/nav&gt;&#xA;&lt;hr&gt;&#xA;&lt;h4 id=&#34;immunomodulatory-effects-of-vitamin-d-and-zinc-on-viral-infection&#34;&gt;Immunomodulatory Effects of Vitamin D and Zinc on Viral Infection&lt;/h4&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Biological Trace Element Research March 2024 &lt;a href=&#34;https://doi.org/10.1007/s12011-024-04139-y&#34;&gt;https://doi.org/10.1007/s12011-024-04139-y&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;PDF is behind a paywall, but can be viewed at &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.deepdyve.com/lp/springer-journals/immunomodulatory-effects-of-vitamin-d-and-zinc-on-viral-infection-qHGjjRn7ok?articleList=%2Fsearch%3Fquery%3D%2522Immunomodulatory%2BEffects%2Bof%2BVitamin%2BD%2Band%2BZinc%2Bon%2BViral%2BInfection%2522&#34;&gt;DeepDyve&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Muhammad Rizwan, Ke Cheng, Yang Gang, Yuntao Hou &amp;amp; Chunfang Wang&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;img src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/attachments/d3.mock.jpg&#34; alt=&#34;image&#34; width=&#34;800&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;img src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/attachments/d3.mock.jpg&#34; alt=&#34;image&#34; width=&#34;800&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Several nutrients are crucial in enhancing the immune system and preserving the structural integrity of bodily tissue barriers. Vitamin D (VD) and zinc (Zn) have received considerable interest due to their immunomodulatory properties and ability to enhance the body’s immune defenses. Due to their antiviral, anti-inflammatory, antioxidative, and immunomodulatory properties, the two nutritional powerhouses VD and Zn  &lt;strong&gt;are crucial for innate and adaptive immunity&lt;/strong&gt; . As observed with COVID-19, deficiencies in these micronutrients impair immune responses, increasing susceptibility to viral infections and severe disease. Ensuring an adequate intake of VD and Zn emerges as a promising strategy for fortifying the immune system. Ongoing clinical trials are actively investigating their potential therapeutic advantages.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Need 2X Vitamin D and other micronutrients if eat 2X more calories</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/posts/need-2x-vitamin-d-and-other-micronutrients-if-eat-2x-more-calories/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 24 Dec 2023 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/posts/need-2x-vitamin-d-and-other-micronutrients-if-eat-2x-more-calories/</guid>
      <description>&lt;nav id=&#34;TableOfContents&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;ul&gt;&#xA;    &lt;li&gt;&#xA;      &lt;ul&gt;&#xA;        &lt;li&gt;&#xA;          &lt;ul&gt;&#xA;            &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#the-science-of-micronutrients-in-clinical-practice--report-on-the-espen-symposium&#34;&gt;The science of micronutrients in clinical practice – Report on the ESPEN symposium&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;            &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#note-most-farmers-and-vets-know-this-but-very-few-doctors&#34;&gt;Note: Most farmers and vets know this, but very few doctors&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;          &lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;        &lt;/li&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/li&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;/nav&gt;&#xA;&lt;hr&gt;&#xA;&lt;h4 id=&#34;the-science-of-micronutrients-in-clinical-practice--report-on-the-espen-symposium&#34;&gt;The science of micronutrients in clinical practice – Report on the ESPEN symposium&lt;/h4&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;ESPEN ENDORSED RECOMMENDATION| VOL 43, # 1, P268-283, Jan 2024  &lt;a href=&#34;https://doi.org/10.1016/j.clnu.2023.12.006&#34;&gt;https://doi.org/10.1016/j.clnu.2023.12.006&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;img src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/attachments/d3.mock.jpg&#34; alt=&#34;image&#34; width=&#34;400&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Background &amp;amp; aims&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The European Society for Clinical Nutrition and Metabolism published its first clinical guidelines for use of micronutrients (MNs) in 2022. A two-day web symposium was organized in November 2022 discussing how to apply the guidelines in clinical practice. The present paper reports the main findings of this symposium.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
